'''Khalid Abdul Mumin Suleman''' (born 6 June 1998), commonly known as '''Abdul Mumin''', is a Ghanaian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Rayo Vallecano]] and the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]].

==Club career==
===Youth===
Mumin was born in [[Accra]] and was a part of the academy at [[Right to Dream Academy|Right to Dream]]. The defender was an integral part of the RtD U18 team, helping them win back-to-back Gothia Cup tournaments in 2014 and in 2015.<ref>{{cite web | title = ABDUL MUMIN SIGNS PRO CONTRACT WITH FC NORDSJÆLLAND | url = http://righttodream.com/abdul-mumin-signs-pro-contract-with-fc-nordsjaelland/ | publisher = righttodream.com | date = 2 August 2016 | access-date = 1 October 2016 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20161105100011/http://righttodream.com/abdul-mumin-signs-pro-contract-with-fc-nordsjaelland/ | archive-date = 5 November 2016 | url-status = dead }}</ref>

===FC Nordsjælland===
On 2 August 2016, it was confirmed, that Mumin had signed a professional contract with [[Danish Superliga]] side [[FC Nordsjælland]], and joined their U19 squad.<ref>{{ cite web | title = FC Nordsjælland skriver med ung ghaneser | url = http://www.bold.dk/fodbold/nyheder/fc-nordsjaelland-skriver-med-ung-ghaneser/ | publisher = bold.dk | date = 2 August 2016}}</ref>

Mumin made his Nordsjælland debut on 7 August 2016, just a few days after signing with the club. Mumin started on the bench, but replaced [[Viktor Tranberg]] in the 62nd minute in a 2–1 defeat against [[AaB Fodbold|AaB]] in the Danish Superliga.<ref>{{ cite web | title = NORDSJÆLLAND VS. AAB  1 - 2 | url = https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/08/07/denmark/superliga/fc-nordsjalland/aalborg-bk/2238296/ | publisher = soccerway.com | date = 7 August 2016}}</ref>

He was promoted to the first team squad for the 2017–18 season. After Nordsjælland sold [[Andreas Skovgaard]] in January 2019, Mumin began to play continuously.

====Loan to HB Køge====
On 23 January 2018, Mumin was loaned out to [[Danish 1st Division]] club [[HB Køge]] for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite web | title = HB Køge henter talentfuld forsvarer i FC Nordsjælland | url = http://hbkoge.dk/Default.aspx?ID=47&Action=1&NewsId=7424&PID=150 | publisher = hbkoge.dk | date = 22 January 2018 | access-date = 23 January 2018 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180818020933/http://hbkoge.dk/Default.aspx?ID=47&Action=1&NewsId=7424&PID=150 | archive-date = 18 August 2018 | url-status = dead }}</ref>

===Vitória de Guimarães===
On 15 August 2020, Portuguese [[Primeira Liga]] club [[Vitória S.C.]] signed Mumin on a four-year deal.<ref>{{cite web |title=Abdul Mumin assina até 2024 |url=https://www.vitoriasc.pt/pt/news/index/view/abdul-mumin-assina-ate-2024 |website=VitoriaSC.pt |publisher=[[Vitória S.C.]] |accessdate=15 August 2020 |date=15 August 2020 |archive-date=19 September 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919193832/https://vitoriasc.pt/pt/news/index/view/abdul-mumin-assina-ate-2024 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Bye Marboe |first1=Mads |title=Officielt: Abdul Mumin skifter til portugisisk klub |url=https://www.tipsbladet.dk/nyhed/generelle/officielt-abdul-mumin-skifter-til-portugisisk-klub |website=Tipsbladet.dk |publisher=[[Tipsbladet]] |accessdate=15 August 2020 |date=15 August 2020}}</ref> Mumin got shirt number 6 and made his official debut for the club in the Primeira Liga on 18 September 2020 against [[Belenenses SAD]], playing all 90 minutes.<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/09/18/portugal/portuguese-liga-/vitoria-guimaraes/clube-futebol--os-belenenses/3355301/ VITORIA GUIMARAES VS. BELENENSES  0 - 1], soccerway.com, 18 September 2020</ref>

===Rayo Vallecano===
On 1 September 2022, Mumin signed a four-year contract with [[La Liga]] side [[Rayo Vallecano]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rayovallecano.es/noticia/abdul-mumin-nuevo-jugador-del-rayo-vallecano|title=Abdul Mumin nuevo jugador del Rayo Vallecano|trans-title=Abdul Mumin new player of Rayo Vallecano|publisher=Rayo Vallecano|language=es|date=1 September 2022|accessdate=2 September 2022}}</ref> Mumin got his debut for the Spanish side on 17 September 2022 against [[Athletic Bilbao]].<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2022/09/17/spain/primera-division/athletic-club/rayo-vallecano/3811479/ ATHLETIC BILBAO VS. RAYO VALLECANO  3 - 2], soccerway.com, 17 September 2022</ref>

On 1 March 2025, Mumin sustained a [[Anterior cruciate ligament injury|cruciate ligament injury]] in a match against [[Sevilla F.C.|Sevilla]], which was expected to keep him sidelined for an extended period.<ref>[https://www.golatv.com/post/abdul-mumin-se-pierde-todo-lo-que-queda-de-temporada Abdul Mumin se pierde todo lo que queda de temporada], golatv.com, 5 March 2025</ref>

==International career==
At the end of December 2021, Mumin received his first call-up to the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]], being summoned to the squad for the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]] in January 2022.<ref>[https://footy-ghana.com/2021/12/afcon-2021-europe-based-mumin-samed-land-ghana-call-ups/ Abdul Mumin, Abdul Samed earn debut Black stars call-up] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220119142139/https://footy-ghana.com/2021/12/afcon-2021-europe-based-mumin-samed-land-ghana-call-ups/ |date=19 January 2022 }}, footy-ghana.com, 21 December 2021</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=2021 Afcon: Ghana to name final squad for tournament on December 30|url=https://www.modernghana.com/sports/1128575/2021-afcon-ghana-to-name-final-squad-for-tourname.html|access-date=6 February 2022|website=Modern Ghana|language=en}}</ref>

Mumin made his debut on 6 June 2024 in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF Group I|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Mali national football team|Mali]] at the [[Stade du 26 Mars]]. He substituted [[Alidu Seidu]] in the 79th minute, Ghana won 2–1 through an added-time goal by [[Jordan Ayew]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=ESPN|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match/_/gameId/687355/|title=Mali v Ghana game report|date=6 June 2024}}</ref>

